The paper discusses bidimensionality theory, which is a framework for the development of metaalgorithmic techniques for problems on graphs. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories related to graph algorithms and computational complexity. cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a likely category as it covers the design and analysis of algorithms, which is a key aspect of bidimensionality theory. cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as bidimensionality theory has been used to obtain results in this area. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possible category as the paper discusses the complexity of problems on graphs. cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with combinatorial problems on graphs. Finally, cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory) is a possible category as the paper discusses approximation algorithms, which are often used in game theory.
